cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on network security and preventing human errors in network management. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the synthesis of network configurations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper presents a tool for automated network configuration synthesis. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a theorem prover (Isabelle/HOL) for formal verification of the tool. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a theorem prover for formal verification.
